TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Role of Robust Optimization in Single-Leg Airline Revenue Management
AU  - Birbil, Ş. İlker
AU  - Frenk, J. B. G.
AU  - Gromicho, Joaquim A. S.
AU  - Zhang, Shuzhong
Y1  - 2009/01/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1070.0843
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1070.0843
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 148
EP  - 163
VL  - 55
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In this paper, we introduce robust versions of the classical static and dynamic single-leg seat allocation models. These robust models take into account the inaccurate estimates of the underlying probability distributions. As observed by simulation experiments, it turns out that for these robust versions the variability compared to their classical counterparts is considerably reduced with a negligible decrease in average revenue.
AB  - In this paper, we introduce robust versions of the classical static and dynamic single-leg seat allocation models. These robust models take into account the inaccurate estimates of the underlying probability distributions. As observed by simulation experiments, it turns out that for these robust versions the variability compared to their classical counterparts is considerably reduced with a negligible decrease in average revenue.
